reviewtext: Gotham City’s favorite vigilante has long been known as “the World’s Greatest Detective.” Matt Reeves is the first director to truly realize that on screen.
I enjoyed Tom Holland as Spider-Man...and Zendaya as MJ but unfortunately I did not like the villain plot...I found it convoluted, predictable and dull
Holland continues to impress, perfectly portraying an awkward boy with incredible superpowers. The comedy in Far From Home is also spot-on.
'Top Gun Maverick' is a one hell of a ride that shouldn't be missed. So hop on and buckle up fast!
For me, The Joker is one of the top features released this year.
Reiterating my love of Scorsese, it's his ability to experiment that makes him a compelling director. Every film he directs is worth the time, and The Irishman lives up to that billing.
Theron turns a stock character into a memorably sinister mix of scorned gold digger and plastic surgery addict. It takes a lot more than a pail of water to wipe out this wicked witch.
It's a very messy movie, but I enjoyed it.
The film achieves a difficult balance. [Full review in Spanish]
Quantumania swings big, but forgets the small stuff, to its own detriment.
